TONIGHT'S BOARD OF EDUCATION MEETING POSTPONED: Due to widespread power outages that are likely to impact the community‚Äôs ability to access tonight‚Äôs Board of Education meeting, we have decided to postpone the meeting to Monday, August 10, at 7 p.m.

Tonight‚Äôs agenda included a presentation about our plans for the fall. We know that this information is extremely important to our stakeholders, therefore the superintendent will be sending LPS families information about our plans for reopening schools later today. The presentation originally prepared for tonight will be made at Monday's meeting, and there will be opportunity for public comment at that time.

post_text: AUGUST 3, 2020 BOARD OF EDUCATION CLOSED EXECUTIVE SESSION: Due to the current health crisis, Livingston Public Schools will continue to hold Board of Education meetings virtually until further notice. On Monday, August 3, 2020 at 6:30 p.m. the Board of Education will hold a closed executive session to discuss legal and personnel issues. All Board of Education meetings must officially open in a public format as required by the Open Public Meetings Act, therefore the meeting will be shown on Facebook Live (@LivSchools) for that very brief portion. However, please note that there will be NO public discussion or participation during tonight's meeting. An open public Board of Education meeting will be held on Wednesday, August 5, at 6:30 p.m. which will include time for public comment. View the closed session agenda @ https://www.livingston.org/site/handlers/filedownload.ashx?moduleinstanceid=45354&dataid=107398&FileName=Agenda%2008-03-20%20-%20Google%20Docs.pdf

post_text: CALENDAR CHANGE: The Board of Education approve a revised 2020-2021 Academic Calendar at last night‚Äôs meeting. The first day of school for students will now be Tuesday, September 8, 2020. This is two days later than originally scheduled on the 2020-2021 calendar. The two Professional Development (PD) days that were scheduled for October and February have been moved to September. Staff will start on September 1, 2020. This will give faculty more time to prepare their classrooms and engage in important PD programs regarding in-person and virtual instruction. July 28, 2020, 6:30PM BOARD OF EDUCATION MEETING/WEBINAR: Due to the current health crisis, we will continue to hold Board of Education meetings virtually until further notice. Meetings will be held in a webinar format during which participants will have the ability to ask questions and make comments. The meetings will be livestreamed on this Facebook page. Registration is required. Click the link below to register for the meeting. The agenda can be found on the district website, www.livingston.org.

Members of the public who are not able to participate in the webinar may email questions/comments, with their NAME and ADDRESS to mbent@livingston.org before or during the meeting. The questions/comments that are emailed in will be read to the Board during the Public Comment portion of the meeting. Please note that the Board will not be communicating through the livestream comments on Facebook. https://zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_GWgEd5VoS6C83sgF0AMMAA

DEADLINE TO SUBMIT NOMINATING PETITION IS 4PM ON JULY 27: In November, Livingston voters will elect one candidate to serve on the Board of Education for three years. Those who wish to become candidates must file a nominating petition with the county clerk for his or her name to appear on the ballot during the annual school election. The deadline to submit the petition is 4 p.m. on Monday, July 27, 2020. The election is scheduled for Tuesday, November 3, 2020.
https://www.njsba.org/about/membership/membership-school-board-members/school-board-candidacy/?_cldee=c3JvYmluc29uQGxpdmluZ3N0b24ub3Jn&recipientid=contact-7d36a3a0a13cea119c3900155d234400-6c7a7566f3874ed1af0c8e21d4d4254c&esid=937c2f1f-799b-ea11-9c44-00155d10129b

June 15, 2020, 7PM BOARD OF EDUCATION MEETING/WEBINAR: Due to the current health crisis, we will continue to hold Board of Education meetings virtually until further notice. Meetings will be held in a webinar format during which participants will have the ability to ask questions and make comments. The meetings will be livestreamed on this Facebook page. Registration is required. Click the link below to register for the meeting. The agenda can be found on the district website, www.livingston.org.

Members of the public who are not able to participate in the webinar may email questions/comments, with their NAME and ADDRESS to mbent@livingston.org before or during the meeting. The questions/comments that are emailed in will be read to the Board during the Public Comment portion of the meeting. Please note that the Board will not be communicating through the livestream comments on Facebook.https://us02web.zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_Dq8a88ecRZyvKr4EAQe1pA

DON'T MISS LHS LANCETALKS! Modeled in the vein of a TED conference, LANCETalks is a series of intellectually stimulating and soul-stirring, live presentations, each 13 minutes in length, covering a variety of different subjects, demonstrating so much of what Livingston High School has to offer. The presenters speak from their heart, share life experiences, and certainly make
an impact on those in attendance! Learn more @
https://www.livingston.org/domain/2448

MAY 18, 2020, 7PM BOARD OF EDUCATION MEETING/WEBINAR: Due to the current health crisis, we will continue to hold Board of Education meetings virtually until further notice. Meetings will be held in a webinar format during which participants will have the ability to ask questions and make comments. The meetings will be livestreamed on this Facebook page. Registration is required. Click the link below to register for the meeting. The agenda can be found on the district website, www.livingston.org.

Members of the public who are not able to participate in the webinar may email questions/comments, with their NAME and ADDRESS to mbent@livingston.org before or during the meeting. The questions/comments that are emailed in will be read to the Board during the Public Comment portion of the meeting. Please note that the Board will not be communicating through the livestream comments on Facebook.https://us02web.zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_HNOCFkneSuyCcso3yXSzsA

post_text: TONIGHT! Join the Livingston community today, Sunday April 5th, for LIVINGSTON SINGS, a live virtual concert that promises to be a very special evening, featuring amazing musical performances and cameo appearances from some of our famous LHS alumni, including Jason Alexander, to benefit Livingston Neighbors Helping Neighbors! The live broadcast will be available on New Media Connection Facebook Event: bit.ly/WatchLivingstonSings. If you don't have Facebook then it will be available here: bit.ly/LivingstonSingsWEB
shared_text:
Livingston Sings

New Media Connection was live.
March 30 at 5:40 PM ¬∑

Livingston Sings is a live music-based fundraising initiative brought to you by LTown Lowdown in response to the COVID-19 pandemic.

Together we raise funds for Livingston Neighbors Helping Neighbors (LNHN*). Their mission is to support township residents struggling with unexpected hardship providing short-term financial assistance and a variety of in-kind support.

Donate Now:bit.ly/LivingstonSings
#LivingstonSings

*LNHN includes management of Livingston‚Äôs Community Hunger Outreach Warehouse (CHOW) in partnership with the Livingston Clergy Association and is also an affiliate of Livingston‚Äôs Healthy Community Healthy Youth (HCHY). The LNHN creates opportunities to respectfully help and empower those in need, thereby promoting a strong sense of community and goodwill through its affiliation with HCHY.

TOMORROW'S BOARD OF EDUCATION MEETING:
Due to the current health crisis, we will continue to hold Board of Education meetings virtually until further notice.

On Wed. April 1, 2020 at 4:30 p.m. the Board of Education will hold a closed executive session to discuss negotiations and personnel. At the beginning of the meeting, there will be a VERY BRIEF public portion for the Board to vote on suspending the policy that prohibits the Board from holding a remote executive session. We will be accepting questions/comments on that one public agenda item ONLY for this meeting; email your NAME, ADDRESS and QUESTION/COMMENT to mbent@livingston.org by 4:30 p.m. on Wed. April 1, 2020. The Board will not be communicating through the livestream comments. Please note that the questions/comments that are emailed in will be read to the Board during the meeting.

Visit this Facebook page to view the public portion of the Board of Education's meeting at 4:30 p.m. on Wednesday, April 1, 2020.

The next regular public meeting, which will include budget discussion, will be held on Mon. April 13, 2020.
